Blink
:''This is an article about the [[HTML]] tag. To read about the human function, please see [[*blinks*]]. To read about rainbow blinkies, please see [[Rainbow blinkies]].''
<div style="text-decoration:blink">
'''Blink''' is a wonderul [[HTML]] tag that pisses people off.

This one works <s>sometimes</s> in firefox only:
 <nowiki><blink>text here</blink></nowiki>

This one works <s>always</s> in firefox:
 <nowiki><span style="text-decoration:blink">text here</span></nowiki>

Why not combine the two?
 <nowiki><blink style="text-decoration:blink;">BLINK BLINK BLINK</blink></nowiki>

Better yet, put this in your header and all your blink tags will work (maybe not in [[Apple|webkit]]):
 <nowiki><script type="text/javascript">

<!--

if(document.all){

	window.setInterval(function(){

		var _b=document.all.tags('blink');

		for(x=0;x<_b.length;x++){

			if(_b[x].style.visibility=='hidden'){

				_b[x].style.visibility='visible';

			}else{

				_b[x].style.visibility='hidden';

			}

		}

	},500);

}

//-->

</script>

<style type="text/css"><!--blink{text-decoration:blink;}--></style></nowiki>

